n","1486–Female":"1486–Overleden","1488–Male":"1488–Overleden","1460–Male":"1460–Overleden","about 1480":"circa 1480","1484":"1484","1482":"1482","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","1477":"1477","1488":"1488","Abt 1475":"circa 1475","1476":"1476","1486":"1486","1475":"1475","before 1460":"vóór 1460","b. abt. 1480":"circa 1480","about 1488":"circa 1488","about 1486":"circa 1486","about 1484":"circa 1484","about 1482":"circa 1482",",, England":"Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Wales":"Wales","England":"England","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales"},"en":{"before 1460–":"before 1460–Deceased","1460–Female":"1460–Deceased","1475–Female":"1475–Deceased","1476–Male":"1476–Deceased","1477–Male":"1477–Deceased","1480–Female":"1480–Deceased","1480–Male":"1480–Deceased","1482–Male":"1482–Deceased","1484–Male":"1484–Deceased","1486–Female":"1486–Deceased","1488–Male":"1488–Deceased","1460–Male":"1460–Deceased","about 1480":"about 1480","1484":"1484","1482":"1482","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","1477":"1477","1488":"1488","Abt 1475":"about 1475","1476":"1476","1486":"1486","1475":"1475","before 1460":"before 1460","b. abt. 1480":"about 1480","about 1488":"about 1488","about 1486":"about 1486","about 1484":"about 1484","about 1482":"about 1482",",, England":"England, United Kingdom","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales","England":"England","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Griffith","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Welsh (Carmarthenshire and western England): from the Old Welsh personal name <i>Gruffudd</i>, Old Welsh <i>Grip(p)iud</i>, composed of the elements <i>grip</i>, of uncertain significance, + <i>iud</i> ‘chief, lord’."],"variants":[{"name":"Griffieth","meanings":["Variant of   Griffith  ."]},{"name":"Griff","meanings":["English: topographic name for someone living near a pit or hollow, from Middle English <i>grif</i> ‘pit, hollow, narrow valley’ (Old Norse <i>gryfja</i>), or a habitational name from Griff in Warwickshire, Griffe in Derbyshire, or Griff Farm in Rievaulx, North Yorkshire, all probably named with this word.","Welsh and English: from the Welsh personal name <i>Gryff</i>, a short form of <i>Gruffudd</i>. See   Griffith  .","German: variant of   Greif   1."]},{"name":"Kerfoot","meanings":["English (Lancashire and Cheshire):","habitational name, probably from Carefoot, near Myerscough (Lancashire).","possibly a variant of   Griffith  ."]},{"name":"Griffes","meanings":["Welsh: altered form of   Griffith  ."]},{"name":"Griffeth","meanings":["Altered form of   Griffith  ."]},{"name":"Griffiths","meanings":["Welsh (Glamorgan and western England): Anglicized form of the patronymic <i>(ap) Gruffudd</i>, from Old Welsh <i>Grippiud</i> (see   Griffith  )."]},{"name":"Griffth","meanings":["Variant of   Griffith  ."]},{"name":"Griffitt","meanings":["Altered form of   Griffith  ."]}]},{"name":"Morgan","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized form of Welsh Morcant , traditionally a boy's name. In Britain since the late 1990s the name has become equally popular as a girl's name, perhaps adopted with conscious reference to  King Arthur's  jealous stepsister  Morgan le Fay . Elsewhere in the English-speaking world, especially in North America, where it also enjoys considerable popularity, it is used predominantly for girls."],"variants":[{"name":"Morcant","meanings":["Traditional: composed of an unexplained first element + a second representing the Old Celtic element <i>cant</i> ‘circle; completion’."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Llewellyn","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional: altered form (influenced by <i>llew</i> ‘lion’) of <i>Llywelyn</i>, an ancient name of uncertain derivation. It probably goes back to the Old Celtic name <i>Lugobelinos</i>, the first element of which is <i>Lugu-</i> (the name of a god;  see  Lleu  ); the second is a name-forming element found also in names such as <i>Cunobelinus</i> (<i>Cymbeline</i>). The name was borne by  Llywelyn ap Iorwerth  (  1173–1240 ) and his grandson Llywelyn ap Gruffydd (  d. 1282 ), Welsh princes who for a time united their countrymen in North Wales and led opposition to the power of the Norman barons in South Wales and the Marches."],"variants":[{"name":"Llywellyn","meanings":["Traditional: altered form (influenced by <i>llew</i> ‘lion’) of <i>Llywelyn</i>, an ancient name of uncertain derivation. It probably goes back to the Old Celtic name <i>Lugobelinos</i>, the first element of which is <i>Lugu-</i> (the name of a god;  see  Lleu  ); the second is a name-forming element found also in names such as <i>Cunobelinus</i> (<i>Cymbeline</i>). The name was borne by  Llywelyn ap Iorwerth  (  1173–1240 ) and his grandson Llywelyn ap Gruffydd (  d. 1282 ), Welsh princes who for a time united their countrymen in North Wales and led opposition to the power of the Norman barons in South Wales and the Marches."]},{"name":"Llywelyn","meanings":["(Welsh)  See  Llewelyn ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Morgan William Llewellyn Griffith was born before 1460, in Wales. He had at least 6 sons and 4 daughters with Rachael Morgan."},"et":{"before 1460–":"enne 1460–Surnud","1460–Female":"1460–Surnud","1475–Female":"1475–Surnud","1476–Male":"1476–Surnud","1477–Male":"1477–Surnud","1480–Female":"1480–Surnud","1480–Male":"1480–Surnud","1482–Male":"1482–Surnud","1484–Male":"1484–Surnud","1486–Female":"1486–Surnud","1488–Male":"1488–Surnud","1460–Male":"1460–Surnud","about 1480":"umbes 1480","1484":"1484","1482":"1482","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","1477":"1477","1488":"1488","Abt 1475":"umbes 1475","1476":"1476","1486":"1486","1475":"1475","before 1460":"enne 1460","b. abt. 1480":"umbes 1480","about 1488":"umbes 1488","about 1486":"umbes 1486","about 1484":"umbes 1484","about 1482":"umbes 1482",",, England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, United Kingdom","Wales":"Wales","England":"England","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales"},"fi":{"before 1460–":"ennen vuotta 1460–Kuollut","1460–Female":"1460–Kuollut","1475–Female":"1475–Kuollut","1476–Male":"1476–Kuollut","1477–Male":"1477–Kuollut","1480–Female":"1480–Kuollut","1480–Male":"1480–Kuollut","1482–Male":"1482–Kuollut","1484–Male":"1484–Kuollut","1486–Female":"1486–Kuollut","1488–Male":"1488–Kuollut","1460–Male":"1460–Kuollut","about 1480":"noin 1480","1484":"1484","1482":"1482","1460":"1460","1480":"1480","1477":"1477","1488":"1488","Abt 1475":"noin 1475","1476":"1476","1486":"1486","1475":"1475","before 1460":"ennen vuotta 1460","b. abt. 1480":"noin 1480","about 1488":"noin 1488","about 1486":"noin 1486","about 1484":"noin 1484","about 1482":"noin 1482",",, England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wales, United Kingdom":"Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Wales":"Wales","England":"England","Glamorgan, Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales"},"fr":{"before 1460–":"avant 1460–Décédé","1460–Female":"1460–Décédée","1475–Female":"1475–Décédée","1476–Male":"1476–Décédé","1477–Mal